Somethin about a Stock 5.9L 🤪 Found a new build! This was the exact platform that got me excited about the automotive industry and the possibilities of editing a canvas auto manufacturers make for the average consumer.  Why I love older trucks vs new is that you can NEVER obtain one of these brand new ever again. Older models made and produced have came and went and what’s left on the road is what’s left.  As days go on more and more are taken off the road never to be put back on yet it’s got the same 4 wheels any other vehicle has and will get you to a and b just the same. Anybody can handle a truck payment but if Something’s broke? fix it and you’ll truly have something nobody can have. 10 years from now you’ll wish trucks like this were still around.

This last year and a half was all about building ourselves, it was hard to find true passion in what I once could.  I found myself trapped in a community the internet and YouTube grouped me with & that I found out I was NOTHING LIKE.  I see great potential in things people wouldn’t think twice about.  I never did ANY of this for subscribers or followers, I never liked trying to compete for attention, I’m not in it for the money, I wasn’t in it to have hour long lines for people to talk to me at truck shows or trying to be “somebody”. If you were in those lines or I hope the ones who have talked to me or have met me realize that I’m just me. A regular dude doing exactly what he wants, and I found myself at a complete loss trying to make it in a material world and community I don’t belong.  Truly you cant compete where you dont compare, it’s all about the fact that there’s one unique individual in all of us and I was TIRED of seeing so much repetitiveness and anybody and everybody doing things for “views” or “likes” or followers because somebody else’s vision allowed them to.  Building is my peace and my art, views and followers arnt.  Chasing that to be relevant in a community ultimately made me do things I didn’t want to, and put me in a position where I truly had to work on myself to get my passion back.  It’s hard when you see everybody else doing X,Y, or Z and you think you’re missing something or doing something wrong when you realize that’s not what you personally want anyway.  My dreams arnt yours & your dreams arnt somebody else’s, Think deep about who you are and the life YOU Want and BUILD YOUR LIFE the way you want it!  With that being said, we are going to live the life we deserve because none of us deserve any less! Going back to our roots providing content, inspiration and starting the projects I’ve collected over the years, allowing WHOEVER to watch, follow and this time it’s all about why I started, providing content I couldn’t find myself to help every single one of you build the life you want & help make your dreams come true! @ashleyy.goebell has been the best support I could ask for ❤️ I wouldn’t change it for the world! Here’s to 2024!
